https://chromiumcodereview.appspot.com/10537010/diff/1/chrome/browser/ui/cocoa/omnibox/omnibox_popup_view_mac.mm#newcode127
chrome/browser/ui/cocoa/omnibox/omnibox_popup_view_mac.mm:127: const NSInteger length = nextOffset - static_cast<NSInteger>(i->offset);
Hey Mike! It seems like there are two underlying problems you're trying to address.

#1 Conversion from string16 to NSString.
I think the best thing to do would be to do something like this:
NSString* s = base::SysUTF16ToNSString(matchString);
if ([s length] != matchString.length()) {
  NOTREACHED();
  return nil;
}

#2 That |classifications| has offsets that go beyond the end of matchString. For this you could do something like:
for (....) {
  if (i->offset >= matchString.length()) {
    NOTREACHED();
    return nil;
  }

  nextOffset = 0;
  if (isLast) {
     nextOffset = matchString.length();
  } else {
    nextOffset = (i + 1)->offset;
    if (nextOffset >= matchString.length()) {
      NOTREACHED();
      return nil;
    }
  }
}

What do you think?

I've not made any of the changes you suggested (explained below) but I have enhanced the diagnostic output of the ValidateClassifications function to that we can more easily identify the autocomplete provider that has failed to handle the classification.

